# Do not

## Code & scope

- Smallest diff that solves the task; no speculative features or drive-by refactors
- No duplication — use helpers in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/ANTI_PATTERNS.md`
- One slice or one user request per session unless explicitly asked
- No trivial tests or comments that restate code

## Git & deploy

- **Commit every completed slice** — one conventional commit after gates pass
- Always run `npm run gates` before commit (unit + contract + crud + integration + build)
- Do not push or deploy without explicit user request
- Do not push with failing CI; no force-push or hook skips unless user requests

## Tests

- Add/update tests for each slice per `docs/SLICES.md#per-slice-test-requirements`
- Unit tests mock AI via `lib/test/mock-ai.ts` — no live Gateway in CI
- CRUD tests in `lib/**/*.crud.test.ts` when touching `lib/store.ts`

## When in doubt

Read `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SLICES.md`, and `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`. Ask before large architectural changes.
